properties.NAME: Dunkin
properties.DESCRIPTION: The world’s leading baked goods and coffee chain, serving premium brewed and iced coffee beverages, bagels, breakfast sandwiches, and other baked goods.

properties.NAME: Brookside Local
properties.DESCRIPTION: Thoughtful array of travel essentials, indulgences, and last-minute giftable treats, presented in a space that pays homage to the vibrant local neighborhood of Brookside.

properties.NAME: The Leagues Sports Lounge & Eatery
properties.DESCRIPTION: Featuring KC McCormick Distillery, elevated sports bar dining, and the KC sports experience highlighting the Negro Leagues Baseball Museum’s history and legacy.

properties.NAME: Soiree Steak and Seafood House
properties.DESCRIPTION: Kansas City’s Chef Anita Moore serves soulful Cajun culinary creations, from pasta to grilled plates with signature sides. The restaurant has a rotating exhibit of memorabilia, artifacts, video, and audio from the American Jazz Museum, along with a performance stage for live in-house music performances.

properties.NAME: Salumeria Cervasi Deli
properties.DESCRIPTION: Like many who trace their heritage back to the old country, a love of authentic food has been a tradition in the Cervasi family since the 1900s. Their family roots can be traced to Sicily, which is an underlying theme in the selection, quality, and variety of offerings from sandwiches, artisan and aged cheeses, and pastas.

properties.NAME: Urban Café
properties.DESCRIPTION: Sit-down dining featuring fresh, healthy, organic small plates, salads, sandwiches, and grilled entrees with a lineup of wine, beer, and cocktails from the local restaurateur team of Justin and Rashaun Clark.

properties.NAME: &GO
properties.DESCRIPTION: Powered by Amazon’s Just Walk Out technology, travelers use a credit card to easily pick up and automatically pay for in-demand travel beauty and health essentials, and tasty packaged sandwiches and snacks to go

properties.NAME: Safi Fresh
properties.DESCRIPTION: This menu offers something for everyone – it includes a wide variety of salads, wraps, and bowls, and a children’s menu. Kansas City’s Chef Laronda Lanear is passionate about healthy eating, health, wellness, and fresh, organic foods and developed Safi Fresh at MCI to provide fresh, healthy, and delicious food served quickly.

properties.NAME: Hearth Locavore Kitchen
properties.DESCRIPTION: Dine-in or grab-and-go items featuring the best from Kansas City’s local farms, ranches, and producers. Artisan cheeses, spices, specialty meats, and spirits are featured in starters, entrees, and suggested beverage pairings.

properties.NAME: Smoothie King
properties.DESCRIPTION: Clean, lower-sugar smoothies with a menu made just for you — with countless combinations of whole fruits, organic veggies, and nutritional enhancers for endless ways to Rule the Day.

properties.NAME: Dunkin
properties.DESCRIPTION: The world’s leading baked goods and coffee chain, serving premium brewed and iced coffee beverages, bagels, breakfast sandwiches, and other baked goods.

properties.NAME: Martin City Brewing
properties.DESCRIPTION: The MCB microbrewery taproom experience at MCI offers local brews complemented by hand-tossed pizzas, sandwiches, and salads. A KC original, Martin City Brewery started with two friends who had a passion for great beer and home-brewing. This dream grew into four pizza and taproom locations across KC and the Coast-to-Coast Pub in Martin City.

properties.NAME: The Market at 18th & Vine
properties.DESCRIPTION: Offering a broad range of travel convenience items, including news, magazines and books, beverages, sweets, chips, snacks, health and beauty products, locally sourced gifts, collectibles, and souvenirs.  Building on the excitement and spirit of the City’s historic jazz district, 18th & Vine Essentials celebrates the intricacies of what makes the 18th & Vine so special.

properties.NAME: Messenger Coffee Co.
properties.DESCRIPTION: Messenger Coffee is a Kansas City locally based artisan coffee roaster offering their coffee roast creations with fresh brewed and specialty coffees, along with pastries and grab-and-go goodies.

properties.NAME: Parisi Coffee
properties.DESCRIPTION: Arguably one of Kansas City’s best specialty coffee concepts featuring handcrafted espresso beverages, teas & treats, and a fresh breakfast, brunch, and lunch offering.

properties.NAME: Grapes & Grains
properties.DESCRIPTION: A Missouri Artisan Wine & Spirits experience that elevates the traditional wine bar with cozy, sophisticated seating in a 360-degree open-air setting with diverse local wines, spirits, and share plates, and a focus on 100% locally sourced ingredients.

properties.NAME: Delta Sky Club
properties.DESCRIPTION: The 11,000-square-foot Club features two all-weather Sky Decks, and is located in Concourse B, north end, mezzanine. The Club boasts some of the best views from the terminal, and features a bar with premium cocktails, seating and charging spaces, and varied dining options. The Delta Sky Club is the place to be to get away from it all while you wait for your flight.

properties.NAME: Guy's Pub & Deli
properties.DESCRIPTION: Known for their original KC-made potato chips, a convenient stop for tasty sandwiches, beer, and cocktails.

properties.NAME: Stockyards Brewing Co.
properties.DESCRIPTION: Good unpretentious craft beers and spirits for hardworking people brought to MCI from the Kansas City favorite brewery located in the historic Stockyards District.

properties.NAME: Directors Cut Take 2 Barbershop
properties.DESCRIPTION: Coming Soon: A unique spa and salon experience inspired by Armon Lasker’s original The Director’s Cut located in the historic 18th & Vine neighborhood. This location pays homage to the jazz experience in the inviting interiors and offers men’s and women’s haircuts, styling, spa services, and a range of styling products.

properties.NAME: 18th & Vine Travel Essentials
properties.DESCRIPTION: Offering travel convenience amenities and services that celebrate Kansas City’s greatest historic entertainment district, with specialty memorabilia such as hats and apparel that celebrates the rich history of KC and local grab & go creations like craft sodas and popcorn.

properties.NAME: Made of KC Food Hall
properties.DESCRIPTION: In the Made of Kansas City Food Hall, restaurants and bars are included that were created in Kansas City, have Kansas City Owners, and are found nowhere else other than Kansas City. Locations include Bloom Baking Co., Jay “Hootie” McShann’s Blues Bar, Poíō, The Hungry Hatch, Bo Lings.

properties.NAME: Big Chicken
properties.DESCRIPTION: From crispy chicken sandwiches and tenders to Cheez-It® crusted mac n’ cheese, each menu item tells a story, all while offering guests an inside look into the life and personality of Shaquille O’Neal. Big Chicken delivers a menu that fuses fame basketball star, Shaquille O’Neal's home-cooked childhood favorites with bold new flavors.

properties.NAME: Meat Mitch
properties.DESCRIPTION: After years of perfecting his barbecue craft on the competition circuit, Mitch Benjamin, Meat Mitch Barbecue owner, has opened his newest location at the Kansas City airport. Featuring fan favorites, such as 16-hour smoked Black Angus hand-carved brisket, his famous burnt ends, and pork ribs for dining in or grabbing to take back home on your flight.

properties.NAME: City Market Coffee Roasters
properties.DESCRIPTION: City Market Coffee Roasters brings historic Kansas City Market’s coffee shop staple to the KCI traveler and is the largest KC small batch roastery that features fresh crop specialty coffees from around the world and is a community favorite from local Nikole Ammer.

properties.NAME: Auntie Anne's
properties.DESCRIPTION: Fresh, hot-out-of-the-oven pretzel snacks paired with refreshing drinks are the next-level snack you deserve anywhere. Unmistakably butter-brushed and baked golden brown pretzels are formed into twists & bite-sized nuggets that are easy to eat for on-the-go lives.

properties.NAME: The Pitch
properties.DESCRIPTION: Inspired by Kansas City’s independent source for news and culture, The Pitch KC features an array of reading materials, including local and national publications, collectibles from local artisans, and healthy and indulgent snacks and beverages.

properties.NAME: Brown & Loe
properties.DESCRIPTION: A culinary cornerstone of City Market, Brown & Loe at KC’s new terminal offers a dine-in experience with a New American menu with dishes accented by French and Italian flavors.

properties.NAME: Lego
properties.DESCRIPTION: A home at the new terminal for the world’s most sought-after toy brand, with a range of activity sets, bricks, and licensed gifts available, and connections to KC’s Legoland Discovery Center.

properties.NAME: Made in KC
properties.DESCRIPTION: A premier retail destination designed as a celebration of Kansas City for locally crafted goods, gifts, and apparel from local artisanal vendors – unique souvenirs, apothecary, fashion, licensed sports merchandise, gourmet confectionary, local grab & go snacks.

properties.NAME: InMotion
properties.DESCRIPTION: Award-winning premium airport electronics retailer offering brands including Beats, Bose, JBL, and Sony across a wide range of products - from noise-canceling headphones to tablets, portable speakers, VR systems, and mobile accessories.

properties.NAME: Turn The Page
properties.DESCRIPTION: Inspired by the mission of Turn the Page KC, a nonprofit organization dedicated to equal literacy for Kansas City youth, we have created a space where books come alive. The oversized book installation at the ceiling, featuring “Our Home Kansas City” by Scott Brown, draws travelers in towards the books and magazines, creating an atmosphere of discovery and inclusion.

properties.NAME: City Market Food Hall
properties.DESCRIPTION: Bringing the sights, sounds, aromas, and attractions from KC’s historic City Market to Concourse B Node. Locations in the Food Hall include Bo Lings, Taste of Brazil, Boulevard Brewing Company Beer Hall, Pigwich, and Buffalo State Pizza Co.

properties.NAME: Cinnabon
properties.DESCRIPTION: Offering reliably delicious and delectable cinnamon buns beloved everywhere.

properties.NAME: Johnston & Murphy
properties.DESCRIPTION: Legacy men’s and women’s footwear, apparel, outerwear, and accessories brand, with quality craftsmanship, world-class customer service, and free shipping options for travelers on the go.

properties.NAME: Aeguana
properties.DESCRIPTION: Premium automated retail vending solutions featuring beauty, electronics, travel convenience, and health and safety items.

properties.NAME: Bo Lings
properties.DESCRIPTION: Richard and Theresa Ng’s Kansas City favorite authentic Chinese dishes from their beloved restaurant concept found across the city.

properties.NAME: Boulevard Brewing
properties.DESCRIPTION: A KC original Boulevard Brewing Co. Beer Hall offers a wide range or artisanal beers complemented by hand-tossed pizzas, sandwiches, and salads.

properties.NAME: Buffalo State Pizza Co.
properties.DESCRIPTION: Ridiculously large pizza slices, unique topping creations, fun atmosphere, and great local and regional craft beers on tap.

properties.NAME: Pigwich
properties.DESCRIPTION: Alex Pope celebrated KC chef who founded Local Pig and Pigwich is now bringing his delicious menu to MCI with gourmet sandwiches, salads, snacks, and daily specials.

properties.NAME: Taste of Brazil
properties.DESCRIPTION: Bold, unique flavors of Brazilian specialty cuisine, including shredded beef pot roast, rissoles, and coxinhas. Brought to you by Marco Rabello and Cristian Maciel, both from Sao Paulo, Brazil.

properties.NAME: Bloom Baking Co.
properties.DESCRIPTION: Serving scratch-made breads, Danish, cakes, and pastries. Sarah Darby is in the business of serving the Kansas City area with ingredients that are sourced locally. While visiting Kansas City Bloom Baking Co. can also be found in the Kansas City’s Historic City Market.

properties.NAME: Jay 'Hootie' McShann's Blues Bar
properties.DESCRIPTION: Pays homage to this founding father of the Kansas City Blues and Jazz Sound. His music will be celebrated through memorabilia and artifacts. Guests can order from the food hall and dine at the bar and order wines, spirits, and beers from local vendors.

properties.NAME: Poio
properties.DESCRIPTION: Poio serves a collection of Asian and Mexican flavors through a large selection of tasty sandwiches and sides.

properties.NAME: The Made For KC BBQ Experience Featuring Smoke' n Magic
properties.DESCRIPTION: An immersive dining and performance space where travelers can indulge in Kansas City’s best-known specialties, BBQ, and music. Included in the restaurant experience, the concession operator, Outstanding Hospitality Management Group, and the Kansas City Barbecue Society held the annual “Made for KC BBQ Championship,” with the first annual Grand Champion pitmaster Smoke n’ Magic being awarded the prize purse and licensing to feature their winning BBQ recipes onto the menu and throughout the restaurant for the year. For more information on the Made for KC BBQ Championship, visit: www.madeforkcbbqchampionship

properties.NAME: BBQ Spot
properties.DESCRIPTION: An enticing array of BBQ rubs, seasonings, spices, and sauces mixed, manufactured, and perfected since 1968 in Kansas City.

properties.NAME: Cloud Gazing
properties.DESCRIPTION: Cloud Gazing is located in the New Terminal's concourse Connector, taking advantage of the long open perspective. The custom artwork will include 10 "clouds" with colorful backgrounds, frames with white nylon straps form a barrier-grid animation. This creates the appearance of movement as travelers walk or glide on the moving walkways below. The glass-sided connector offers views of the airfield and sky on both sides, complemented by the custom artwork overhead.

properties.NAME: Fountain (KCI)
properties.DESCRIPTION: Leo Villareal’s Fountain (KCI) is a light sculpture that pays homage to Kansas City’s legacy as The City of Fountains. The artwork transforms this gateway into a welcoming and dynamic environment.

properties.NAME: Wings
properties.DESCRIPTION: Large-scale ceramic wings depicting Kansas and Missouri iconography.

properties.NAME: The Air Up There
properties.DESCRIPTION: "Cloud Gazing" is located in the New Terminal's concourse Connector, taking advantage of the long open perspective. The custom artwork will include 10 ""clouds"" with colorful backgrounds, overlaid with a frame of white nylon straps to form a barrier-grid animation. This will create the appearance of movement as travelers walk or glide on the moving walkways below. The glass-sided connector offers views of the airfield and sky on both sides, complemented by the custom artwork overhead.

properties.NAME: The Hungry Hatch Bowls & Wraps
properties.DESCRIPTION: Healthy grain bowls, wraps and salads inspired by different places around the world. A Kansas City food truck favorite offering healthy fast street food for travelers.

properties.NAME: Mother Earth Coffee Co.
properties.DESCRIPTION: Award-winning espresso and brewed coffee beverages, juices, pastries, and sandwiches to go that are available to KCI meeters and greeters located in the arrivals baggage claim area pre-security.

properties.NAME: &GO
properties.DESCRIPTION: Powered by Amazon’s Just Walk Out technology, travelers use a credit card to easily pick up and automatically pay for in-demand travel beauty and health essentials, and tasty packaged sandwiches and snacks to go

properties.NAME: Everything Travel
properties.DESCRIPTION: Conveniently located “mini store” kiosk stocking last-minute travel essentials and a high-quality mix of hometown favorite branded giftable.

properties.NAME: Bo Lings
properties.DESCRIPTION: Richard and Theresa Ng’s Kansas City favorite authentic Chinese dishes from their beloved restaurant concept found across the city.

properties.NAME: Ornithology
properties.DESCRIPTION: The suspended artwork is a tribute to Kansas City native son, jazz great, Charlie “Yardbird” Parker, and his 1946 tune titled, "Ornithology". Constructed in the historic 18th & Vine District in Kansas City, Ornithology consists of twelve larger than life birds made entirely from alto saxophones.

properties.NAME: Molten Swing
properties.DESCRIPTION: Dichroic acrylic in stainless steel grid panels are suspended in a freeform shape as an ode to KC jazz and Bennie Moten.

properties.NAME: Let the Music Take You
properties.DESCRIPTION: A larger than life ceramic full jazz band of figures and instruments cases line up to check in for a flight. Celebrating Kansas City’s historic jazz culture, ceramics, and love of travel.

properties.NAME: Flights
properties.DESCRIPTION: Flights is a celebration of the improvisational character of Kansas City jazz and the aerodynamic forms that enable flight.

properties.NAME: Sky Prairie
properties.DESCRIPTION: Sky Prairie is a suspended kinetic artwork that takes inspiration from the beautiful rolling hills of the surrounding landscape of Kansas City, containing a plethora of natural and cultured grasses in warm golden hues. The artwork is activated by natural air movements and currents resulting from the movement of cars and buses through the Arrivals Roadway.

properties.NAME: Kansas Braids and Grass Style
properties.DESCRIPTION: I combine my idenity of long black hair with wheatfield and tallgrass to depict the beauty of Kansas nature as well as being a Chinese in the American Midwest.

properties.NAME: Cone Worshiop
properties.DESCRIPTION: A photograph of a tetrahedron (a landing direction indicator and it’s sight cones) at a local airport.

properties.NAME: Diaspora
properties.DESCRIPTION: Multimedia collage and digital storytelling about native lands and people.

properties.NAME: Dreaming of The Beautiful Places You Will Go
properties.DESCRIPTION: My sculpture, “Dreaming Of The Beautiful Places You Will Go" allowed me to communicate my autobiographical narrative of being an artist/educator into this plexiglas sculpture made of digital images of my ceramic built artworks. As a daughter of a florist, I have always been surround by beautiful flowers that inspire my "Dream Clouds".

properties.NAME: Fly-Over Country: The Wild Side
properties.DESCRIPTION: Sometimes referred to as “fly-over” country, the Midwest is home to a variety of ecosystems. This textile work offers a view of the wildlife in the Missouri / Kansas region far below the airplane cabin window. The colorful backdrop of hand-dyed wool comes from the artist’s family farm in rural Missouri.

properties.NAME: Hello and Goodbye
properties.DESCRIPTION: “Hello and Goodbye” documents a fluid state between experience, memory, and place drawn from Liao's immigrant background. Ceramic tiles that capture fragments of memory interrupted once-familiar patterns. Through iterations, the artist revisited images, snapshots, and memories, until they began to morph, overlap, and unravel.

properties.NAME: I Spy Carry-On
properties.DESCRIPTION: These compositions invite the traveler to seek and discover familiar items found in carry-on luggage flowing through the x-ray machine. The project and its title were inspired by the popular I Spy books which present thematic visual riddles.

properties.NAME: Kansas City Reciprocity
properties.DESCRIPTION: Kansas City Reciprocity celebrates the commitment of KCI area farmers to food security, land stewardship, sustainability, ecological diversity, and preservation of cultural heritage. Scan the QR code to identify the produce, see documentation of the artist’s interactions with local farmers, and learn about Kansas City’s supportive food systems.

properties.NAME: Kansas City: A Quilted History
properties.DESCRIPTION: In Kansas City: A Quilted History, Rachel Hubbard Kline celebrates Kansas City's history by combining news stories with quilt patterns sourced from the Kansas City Star and her collection of ancestral quilts. Historical events, as documented in the Kansas City Star and Kansas City Times, appear in relief from laser engravings on clay tiles.

properties.NAME: Midwestern Meanderings
properties.DESCRIPTION: This work depicts, not only the diverse types of people you may meet in KC, but also the changing landscape you experience while driving 30 minutes in any direction.

properties.NAME: Ode to the Tallgrass Prairie
properties.DESCRIPTION: I have investigated the flowers and fauna of the tallgrass prairie which are displayed in this work. Attached to the QR codes are short stories and recipes telling about each of the illustrations.

properties.NAME: Nostalgia
properties.DESCRIPTION: ‘Nostalgia’ is a series of vignettes embracing the nuances of human connection; evanescent rendered eternal by the tangible and intangible threads of shifting seasons, fluid  landscapes, cultural festivities and shared experiences, weaving  moments into memories, making life meaningful.

properties.NAME: People of KC
properties.DESCRIPTION: I chose to paint 5 people of various backgrounds that represent what it means to live in greater KC. I chose 3 women and 2 men. More women than men as the pendulum needs to swing in more of a feminine direction.

properties.NAME: Prairie Confluence
properties.DESCRIPTION: Confluence of sky/land/overview of the Kansas landscape/skyscape, this work is influenced by my time on the prairie and the beautiful lights ive seen.

properties.NAME: Rays
properties.DESCRIPTION: “Rays” depicts an imagined landscape across a vast distance. The shapes within this work refer to the interconnection of the rays of the sun and the growth of uniquely tall grasses in this region of the world.

properties.NAME: Separate and Complex Bodies, Sophisticated Interactions, and Unfathomable Lives
properties.DESCRIPTION: Photographs from parks and green spaces around Kansas City were taken right at the start of spring and collaged together into an imagined landscape.

properties.NAME: Sight Lines, Flight Lines
properties.DESCRIPTION: These four seasons paintings consist of two panels each, one depicting possible views traveling to or from the KCI Airport and the same view as seen from above. Color coded lines indicate the corresponding lines of sight and the passenger plane silhouette points in the direction to the airport.

properties.NAME: Taking Flight
properties.DESCRIPTION: Taking Flight is a triptych depicting the three stages of commercial air travel: liftoff, cruise control, and the final approach. In each panel, passengers engage in casual conversation, soaring through the clouds several miles above sea level. In the last phase of descent, passengers look out the window where silhouetted Monarch butterflies flutter above Kaw Point, the point where the Missouri and Kansas rivers meet, greeting you upon arrival to your destination: Kansas City.

properties.NAME: Woven Landscape Print Series
properties.DESCRIPTION: Like a long walk or a country drive, "Woven Landscape” recognizes how our lives are interwoven with this rich land. Curiosity and desire to see from multiple perspectives, textile artist Debbie Barrett-Jones first wove hand-dyed yarn on a sixteen-harness loom, then hand-sculpted to be photographed for this original print series.

properties.NAME: Kansas City Air Travel Experience
properties.DESCRIPTION: Flight travel can be stressful even for the most seasoned passengers, and possibly overwhelming for first-time travelers or those who are neurodivergent. In addition to navigating the various terminal procedures, boarding the plane itself can present a challenge.    The Kansas City Air Travel Experience Room provides a true-to-life space to gain experience with check-in, security screening, boarding and flight procedures, all in a calm and controlled atmosphere. Users are guided through every step of the air travel experience inside a section of an actual Airbus 320 fuselage, with working overhead storage bins, seat belts, tray tables and lavatory, providing hands-on experience in a safe environment. Through practice, the room can help calm fears and ensure a better, real-life flight experience in the future.

properties.NAME: GRAY BUS – To Rental Car Facility
properties.DESCRIPTION: “Gray Buses” offer free 24/7 transportation between the Consolidated Rental Car Facility and the terminal. Rental Car stops are located on the commercial curb and marked with overhead signs

properties.NAME: ECONOMY BUS - To Economy Parking Lots
properties.DESCRIPTION: "Blue Buses" offer free 24/7 transportation between the Economy Parking Lots and the terminal. Stops are located on the commercial curb outside the terminal and are marked with overhead signs. In the Economy Lots, Blue Buses stop at each covered shelter

properties.NAME: Rideshare Pickup [Purple Signposts]
properties.DESCRIPTION: Kansas City International Airport has a number of transportation services, including app-based ride share services, such as Uber and Lyft. App-based ride share services, including Uber and Lyft, are available through apps on your mobile device. Please wait until you have retrieved your bags and arrived at the Arrivals curb before booking an app-based ride. For pickup, please follow the signs down to the Arrivals commercial curb, and look for the purple signposts 2K-N. There are a limited number of spots available at the designated Ride Share curb, so please wait until you see your vehicle pull into a spot to enter the vehicle

properties.NAME: RIDE KC BUS [Signpost 2A]
properties.DESCRIPTION: RideKC operates to and from Kansas City International Airport every day of the week. The regular fare is free at this time. View the Kansas City International route map here or search RideKC's website for Route #229 at the Boardwalk-KCI transfer station

properties.NAME: Pre-arranged Shuttles [Cross the Road]
properties.DESCRIPTION: See the link below to the VisitKC website where you can research limousine services offering transportation to and from Kansas City International Airport. Before choosing, research your limousine company choice carefully, as the Kansas City Aviation Department does not endorse nor guarantee any particular company

properties.NAME: Taxis
properties.DESCRIPTION: Taxi service can be called using your personal phone by dialing 816-243-2345. Make sure that you give the dispatcher your exact location.   Fares may be prorated (shared) when the originating passenger requests it and all other passengers agree.   Rates are $2.50 plus $2.10 per mile. Rates may vary due to traffic delays and waiting time

properties.NAME: Change is easy
properties.DESCRIPTION: Easy to edit
